The '/std/gettable' inheritable

inherits: nothing

works well with: any base object

Summary: Implements an object which can be picked up, as well as
objects that give custom messages when they are picked up/someone
tries to pick them up.
The flags all work this way: <0, print the message and fail.
                             0, fail with the default message.
                             >0, succeed.

Functions useful in configuring:
set_getmsg(), set_gettable(), set_dropmsg(), set_dropable()

New Functions:
set_getmsg() - sets the message given when someone tries to get 
    the object
query_getmsg() - returns the get message
set_gettable() - if >0, the object can be gotten; if <0, print the
    get message, if 0, print the default get message
query_dropmsg() - returns the drop message
set_dropmsg() - sets the drop message
set_dropable() - if <0, print the drop message, if >0, can be dropped,
    if zero, print default fail message

Overloaded Functions:
get() - check gettable and print message if gettable < 0
drop() - check dropable and print message if dropable < 0
